# bug.0344 — machine-written kustomize overlays.
# These files are rewritten by two non-prettier writers:
#   1. Argo CD Image Updater (main:infra/k8s/overlays/preview/**/kustomization.yaml,
#      via the annotations on preview-applicationset.yaml — see
#      scripts/ci/check-image-updater-scope.sh for the current allowlist).
#   2. scripts/ci/promote-k8s-image.sh (deploy/* branches' overlays), invoked by
#      flight-preview.yml, candidate-flight.yml, and promote-and-deploy.yml.
# Both writers use YAML libraries whose output (unindented list items, compact
# flow-mappings) disagrees with prettier's YAML style. Running prettier against
# these files in CI creates a permanent fight: prettier fixes indent, image-updater
# re-flattens on the next merge, the next PR's format:check fails. These overlays
# carry 3 structural authors (humans, image-updater, promote-k8s-image.sh);
# prettier is simply not one of them. Humans who edit these by hand are free to
# run prettier manually — we just don't gate CI on a format the machines won't
# preserve. See work/items/bug.0344.adopt-digest-update-controller.md § Post-merge
# amendment for the full context.
infra/k8s/overlays/**/kustomization.yaml
